From: Dejin Zheng <zhengdejin5@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 6 Feb 2020 23:29:17 +0800
Subject: net: stmmac: fix a possible endless loop
Git-commit: 7d10f0774f9e32aa2f2e012f7fcb312a2ce422b9
Patch-mainline: 5.6-rc1
References: networking-stable-20_02_09

It forgot to reduce the value of the variable retry in a while loop
in the ethqos_configure() function. It may cause an endless loop and
without timeout.

Fixes: a7c30e62d4b8 ("net: stmmac: Add driver for Qualcomm ethqos")
Signed-off-by: Dejin Zheng <zhengdejin5@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Vinod Koul <vkoul@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-qcom-ethqos.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-qcom-ethqos.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-qcom-ethqos.c
@@ -413,6 +413,7 @@ static int ethqos_configure(struct qcom_
 			dll_lock = rgmii_readl(ethqos, SDC4_STATUS);
 			if (dll_lock & SDC4_STATUS_DLL_LOCK)
 				break;
+			retry--;
 		} while (retry > 0);
 		if (!retry)
 			dev_err(&ethqos->pdev->dev,
